name: Session
description: Use the Cache.Session class to add, retrieve, and manage values in the session cache. The session cache is active as long as the user’s Salesforce session is valid (the user is logged in, and the session is not expired).

contains(string).name: contains
contains(string).description: Returns true if the session cache contains a cached value corresponding to the specified key.

get(string).name: get
get(string).description: Returns the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the session cache.

get(system.type,string).name: get
get(system.type,string).signature: public static Object get(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
get(system.type,string).description: Returns the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the session cache. Use this method if your cached value is a class that implements the CacheBuilder interface.

getavggettime().name: getAvgGetTime
getavggettime().description: Returns the average time taken to get a key from the session cache, in nanoseconds.

getavgvaluesize().name: getAvgValueSize
getavgvaluesize().description: Returns the average item size for keys in the session cache, in bytes.

getcapacity().name: getCapacity
getcapacity().description: Returns the percentage of session cache capacity that has been used.

getkeys().name: getKeys
getkeys().description: Returns all keys that are stored in the session cache and visible to the invoking namespace.

getmaxgettime().name: getMaxGetTime
getmaxgettime().description: Returns the maximum time taken to get a key from the session cache, in nanoseconds.

getmaxvaluesize().name: getMaxValueSize
getmaxvaluesize().description: Returns the maximum item size for keys in the session cache, in bytes.

getmissrate().name: getMissRate
getmissrate().description: Returns the miss rate in the session cache.

getname().name: getName
getname().description: Returns the name of the default cache partition.

getnumkeys().name: getNumKeys
getnumkeys().description: Returns the total number of keys in the session cache.

getpartition(string).name: getPartition
getpartition(string).description: Returns a partition from the session cache that corresponds to the specified partition name.

isavailable().name: isAvailable
isavailable().description: Returns true if the session cache is available for use. The session cache isn’t available when an active session isn’t present, such as in asynchronous Apex or code called by asynchronous Apex. For example, if batch Apex causes an Apex trigger to execute, the session cache isn’t available in the trigger because the trigger runs in asynchronous context.

put(string,object).name: put
put(string,object).signature: public static void put(String key, Object value)
put(string,object).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the session cache. The put method can write only to the cache in your org’s namespace.

put(string,object,cache.visibility).name: put
put(string,object,cache.visibility).signature: public static void put(String key, Object value, Cache.Visibility visibility)
put(string,object,cache.visibility).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the session cache and sets the cached value’s visibility.

put(string,object,integer).name: put
put(string,object,integer).signature: public static void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs)
put(string,object,integer).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the session cache and sets the cached value’s lifetime.

put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.name: put
put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.signature: public static void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs, cache.Visibility visibility, Boolean immutable)
put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the session cache. This method also sets the cached value’s lifetime, visibility, and whether it can be overwritten by another namespace.

remove(string).name: remove
remove(string).description: Deletes the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the session cache.

remove(system.type,string).name: remove
remove(system.type,string).signature: public static Boolean remove(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
remove(system.type,string).description: Deletes the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the session cache. Use this method if your cached value is a class that implements the CacheBuilder interface.
